name: Centennial Glory
description: A very large and heavy sword said to carry justice with it.

name: Water Dragon Boots
description: Blue shoes worn by a fast-moving heroine. Not completely worn through somehow.

name: Sidereal Serendipity
description: A rifle with many more complex moving parts than appears necessary. What are they for?

name: Book of Alexandria
description: Legendary tome that could contain all the world's knowledge.

name: Swordbreaker
description: Knife capable of disrupting enemies' attacks and plans.

name: Magic Fists
description: A set of cable weights designed to look like white-gloved fists. They're very light and the cable is nearly undetectable.

name: Velvet Masque
description: These stained-glass-inspired Tarot cards occasionally give off flickers of blue flame.

name: Fahr Fox
description: A stylish spear with a vague fox motif.

name: Tower of White
description: A long single-edged sword of obviously Eastern make. There are no clues as to who forged it.

name: Toolesque
description: A cold but vibrant blue axe that gives a vaguely divine aura.

name: Death's Eye
description: The favored weapon of a certain young vampire killer. It looks like an ordinary kitchen knife.

name: Angel Heart
description: A very ornate scepter that was apparently once mixed up with a different scepter and a continent.

name: Black Memory
description: The last remnant of someone that was loved. Its previous owner discarded it after coming across a very dark power.

name: Altera Slaves
description: Small constructs that were repurposed into a set of cable weights.

name: Command Stones
description: Heavy tablets inscribed with draconian-looking laws.

name: Chaser WX
description: Alien weapon that responds to elemental energy by altering its firing patterns.

name: Fairy Halberd
description: Cold double-ended polearm. Appears to be futuristic.

name: Hallucination
description: Black-bound tome that deals exclusively in darkness and illusion magic.

name: Key to the City
description: Heavy sword that nonetheless looks like a construct part.

name: Magnoise
description: Extremely large axe that swings wildly around iron deposits.
